'''
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Task / Question                          | Formula / Trick          | Meaning / Use           | Example                     |
+------------------------------------------+---------------------------+--------------------------+------------------------------+
| 1) Check odd/even                        | x & 1                     | 1 → odd, 0 → even        | 7 & 1 = 1 (odd)             |
|                                          |                           |                          | 8 & 1 = 0 (even)            |
+------------------------------------------+---------------------------+--------------------------+------------------------------+
| 2) Check if k-th bit is ON               | x & (1 << k)              | ≠ 0 → bit is ON          | 13 & (1<<2) = 4 → ON        |
+------------------------------------------+---------------------------+--------------------------+------------------------------+
| 3) Set (turn ON) the k-th bit            | x | (1 << k)              | Turns that bit to 1      | 0001 | 1000 = 1001           |
+------------------------------------------+---------------------------+--------------------------+------------------------------+
| 4) Clear (turn OFF) the k-th bit         | x & ~(1 << k)             | Turns that bit to 0      | x & ~0100 clears bit 2      |
+------------------------------------------+---------------------------+--------------------------+------------------------------+
| 5) Extract lowest set bit                | x & -x                    | Gets rightmost 1-bit     | 101100 & 010100 = 000100    |
+------------------------------------------+---------------------------+--------------------------+------------------------------+
| 6) Count set bits (fast method)          | n &= (n - 1) repeatedly   | Removes lowest 1 each time| 1101→1100→1000→0 (3 bits)   |
+------------------------------------------+---------------------------+--------------------------+------------------------------+
| 7) Check if number is power of 2         | (n & (n - 1)) == 0        | True only for 1 set bit  | 8 & 7 = 0 → yes             |
|                                          | and n > 0                 |                          | 10 & 9 ≠ 0 → no             |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

'''
